There is still one task below which it will take a long time to go: how to make someone who is physically in a very small space believe that he is walking in an almost infinite open space - we work on the concepts of treadmills (nothing to do with those found in fitness clubs), mobile platforms and also giant balls.
At the moment, we only manage to deceive the brain on average, there are still many years of work left.
This is what makes the work on virtual reality so interesting for the researcher: many things are still in the absolute state of fertilization.
