They should then possibly explain why they don't want it.
When there is a strong personality who will identify abuses, it will be possible to put pressure on the political scene.
Take, for example, the election of the president by direct suffrage, which was achieved thanks to the pressure of public opinion.
I confess, without ambiguity, to be an amateur, and not a genius or an intellectual.
I'm trying to find allies for my opinions and visions.
I just got into politics and I'm trying to get the majority support for my program.
I'm trying alone to get things moving, and if it doesn't work out, I'm going to stop in six years and go back to the private sector.
It's a bit like Okamura was going to save the Czech Republic.
I'm not a savior.
